MAIN_MESSAGE: There is a power cut in the ML1 postcode area of Motherwell. It has been necessary for our engineers to carry out an emergency shutdown at 9:50am due to emergency underground repairs and this may affect the supply to your property. We will work to get your power back on as quickly and as safely as possible by 4:30pm. We will update this message if this information changes. We apologise for the inconvenience and thank you for your patience. This message was updated at 10:55am on Thursday, 22 April 2021

We apologise for the inconvenience and thank you for your patience. This message was updated at 10:55am on Thursday, 22 April 2021

MAIN_MESSAGE: There is a power cut affecting the KA6 and KA7 postcode area of Ayr and the KA19 postcode area of Maybole. We had no advance warning of this and only became aware of it at 9:43am. Our emergency response team are on site within the local area and have been made aware of a damaged underground cable caused by third party damage near Laigh Grange Farm. Our control centre will attempt to reset the network remotely to restore power in stages. Our team will work to get majority of customers back on by 12pm and remaining customers will be restored, as quickly and as safely as possible by 4pm. We apologise for the inconvenience and thank you for your patience. This message was updated 11:45am on Thursday 22nd April 2021
TRANSCRIPT: There is a power cut affecting the KA6 and KA7 postcode area of Ayr and the KA19 postcode area of Maybole. We had no advance warning of this and only became aware of it at 9:43am. Our emergency response team are on site within the local area and have been made aware of a damaged underground cable caused by third party damage near Laigh Grange Farm. Our control centre will attempt to reset the network remotely to restore power in stages. Our team will work to get majority of customers back on by 12pm and remaining customers will be restored, as quickly and as safely as possible by 4pm. We apologise for the inconvenience and thank you for your patience. This message was updated 11:45am on Thursday 22nd April 2021
